Metadata.CommitMsg:
refactor: update goerr to v2 (#119)

* chore(.gitignore): add .cckiro to .gitignore to exclude unnecessary files from version control

* feat: upgrade goerr to v2 and update error handling patterns across the codebase to improve context and clarity

* fix(client.go): replace goerr.Wrap with goerr.New for better error handling consistency in GitHub client methods
Metadata.Author: Masayoshi Mizutani <mizutani@hey.com>

Vulnerabilities.Title: golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent: in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent
Vulnerabilities.Description: SSH Agent servers do not validate the size of messages when processing new identity requests, which may cause the program to panic if the message is malformed due to an out of bounds read.

Vulnerabilities.Title: golang.org/x/crypto/ssh: in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh
Vulnerabilities.Description: SSH servers parsing GSSAPI authentication requests do not validate the number of mechanisms specified in the request, allowing an attacker to cause unbounded memory consumption.
